article.headline: Murray St. 88, Tennessee St. 58
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. -- Danero Thomas scored 17 points on 7-of-9 shooting to lead Murray State to an 88-58 win over Tennessee State on Wednesday night. The Racers (11-9, 6-4 Ohio Valley Conference) shot 59.3 percent from the field (32-for-54), including 82.6 percent in the second half (19-for-23). Donte Poole scored 15, and Ivan Aska added 14. Murray State only led 34-30 at halftime, but used a 21-2 run to start the second half, jumping out to a 55-32 lead with 12:15 remaining. The Tigers (6-16, 4-8) never recovered, and trailed by at least 21 points the rest of the way. Tennessee State was led by Gerald Robinson and Wil Peters, who scored 13 points apiece. Jerrell Houston chipped in with 10 points and seven rebounds. Murray State outrebounded Tennessee State 35-25.
